 <section id="tribute-info">
   
   <h3 id="headline info"> Here is a timeline of Klaus Obermeyer's life and achievements</h3>

<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>1919</strong> - Born in Oberstaufen,           Germany</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>1947</strong> - Moves to Aspen, Colorado        and becomes a ski instructor. It was this job that lead to the founding of his company Sport Obermeyer in the same year.</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>1961</strong> - The first Obermeyer warehouse is opened in Aspen, Colorado</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>1985</strong> - Awarded the Pioneer of Skiing Governor's Cup</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>1997</strong> - Inducted into the Colorado Ski Hall of Fame</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>2001</strong> - Inducted into the Aspen Hall of Fame</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>2004</strong> - Aspen News Businessman of the Year</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>2006</strong> - Aspen Business of the Year</li>
  
  <li>
    <strong>2015</strong> - Inducted into the Colorado Business Hall of Fame</li>

  <li>
    <strong>2019</strong> - Gov. Jared Polis deems January 29th "Klaus Obermeyer Day"</li>
      
      </ul>
    
<blockquote
  cite="https://coloradosun.com/2019/01/30/aspen-innovator-klaus-obermeyer-still-skiing-at-age-99-celebrated-at-outdoor-retailer-snow-show-kickoff/"
  >
  
  <p>
    "Our great freedom in life is that of our own perception."
  </p>
  <cite>-- Klaus Obermeyer</cite>
   </blockquote>
  
